Pre-Game Insights: Head coach of the senior national team of Nigeria, Finidi George, has made three changes to the team that drew 1-1 against South Africa in their world cup qualifiers game on Friday.
Finidi’s team came from behind to draw 1-1, a result that leaves them 5th in the six-team group and two points behind group leaders Lesotho.
The newly appointed coach has made changes to his starting lineup in reaction to the draw against South Africa.
Kelechi Iheanacho has been dropped from the starting lineup with Samuel Chukwueze certain to start in his place.
Raphael Onyedika, who impressed after coming on as a substitute on Friday, is included in the starting lineup.
Benjamin Tanimu keeps his spot in the starting lineup for today’s game with Chidozie Awaziem remaining on the bench.
The game will start at 5pm Nigerian time.
